headline: Looking At The Narrative For HELLENiQ ENERGY Holdings (ATSE:ELPE) After Mixed Analyst Revisions
summary: The latest research on HELLENiQ ENERGY Holdings points to a slightly revised fair value estimate, edging from €8.78 to about €8.80, alongside a lower discount rate assumption at about 10.16% compared with 10.72% previously. These updates sit against a backdrop of optimism around refining fundamentals on one side and concerns about execution and share price performance on the other, with revenue growth expectations now set at about 39.40% instead of 44.02%. headline: America’s oldest bank bets big on AI
summary: America’s oldest bank is going all in on AI. BNY spends nearly $4 billion a year on technology, or about 19 percent of its revenue – a proportion far higher than any of its big-bank peers. But the big concern around the bank industry’s AI spending right now is what the return will be. CNBC’s Leslie Picker dives into BNY’s latest AI efforts and what it could mean for the future of the firm.
